FBIS3-7572 "dreas061__a94012" FBIS-EAS-94-061-A Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 ANNEX Japan Party Leaders Consider Formation of New Party Hosokawa Denies Reports OW3003110494 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 29 Mar 94 Evening Edition p 3--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW3003110494 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN Language: Japanese Article Type:BFN [Text] At a news conference on the morning of 29 March, Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa was asked about a news report that an agreement has been reached between Shinseito [Japan Renewal Party] Chief Secretary Ichiro Ozawa, Komeito Secretary General Yuichi Ichikawa, and Hosokawa that they will work to form a new party for which "Hosokawa would serve as representative and Ozawa as secretary general." In reply, Hosokawa denied the report, saying: "It was a complete surprise to me. I am greatly annoyed by that report." When asked about the current situation in which many reports have been circulated on the issue of forming a new party, Hosokawa said, "I cannot answer the question because I am devoted entirely to official business."
